---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | ISJ Jakarta"
  description="Privacy Policy for The Independent School of Jakarta. How ISJ collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
  canonicalUrl="/privacy"
>

  <section class="pt-32 lg:pt-40 section-pad px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--content-narrow)]">
      <p class="label mb-5">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-[length:var(--text-2xl)] font-light text-navy leading-[1.1] mb-10">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-[length:var(--text-xs)] text-charcoal-muted mb-12">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-charcoal-light leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Introduction</h2>
          <p>The Independent School of Jakarta ("ISJ") is committed to protecting the privacy of families, prospective families, staff, and visitors. This policy explains how ISJ collects, uses, and safeguards your personal data.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">For data protection purposes, ISJ is the data controller.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">What Data ISJ Collects</h2>
          <p>ISJ may collect the following information:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 pl-1">
            <li>Names, contact details, and addresses of parents and children</li>
            <li>Date of birth and nationality of prospective pupils</li>
            <li>Previous school history and academic records</li>
            <li>Health and medical information relevant to your child's welfare</li>
            <li>Contact form submissions and tour booking requests</li>
            <li>Website usage data through cookies and analytics</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">How ISJ Uses Your Data</h2>
          <p>ISJ uses personal data for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 pl-1">
            <li>Processing admissions enquiries and applications</li>
            <li>Arranging campus tours and responding to questions</li>
            <li>Administering your child's education, welfare, and safety</li>
            <li>Communicating with families about school life and events</li>
            <li>Meeting ISJ's legal and regulatory obligations</li>
            <li>Improving the website and services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
          <p>ISJ processes personal data on the following bases: performance of a contract (enrolment and education), legitimate interests (responding to enquiries, school administration), legal obligation (safeguarding, regulatory compliance), and consent (marketing communications, cookies).</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Sharing Your Data</h2>
          <p>ISJ does not sell personal data. ISJ may share data with: Indonesian regulatory authorities as required by law, third-party service providers who process data on ISJ's behalf (such as email providers and analytics tools), and professional advisers where necessary.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Data Retention</h2>
          <p>ISJ retains personal data only for as long as necessary for the purposes described in this policy, or as required by law. Enquiry data is retained for two years. Pupil records are retained in accordance with Indonesian education regulations.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Your Rights</h2>
          <p>You have the right to access, correct, or request deletion of your personal data. You may also object to processing or request restriction of processing. To exercise these rights, contact ISJ at <a href="mailto:info@isj.id" class="whisper-link">info@isj.id</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Cookies</h2>
          <p>The ISJ website uses cookies to improve your experience. See the <a href="/cookies" class="whisper-link">Cookie Policy</a> for details.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-[length:var(--text-base)] text-navy font-medium mb-3">Contact</h2>
          <p>If you have questions about this policy or how ISJ handles your data, please contact ISJ at <a href="mailto:info@isj.id" class="whisper-link">info@isj.id</a> or write to: The Independent School of Jakarta, Jl. R.A. Kartini No. Kav. 12, Pondok Indah, South Jakarta 12310, Indonesia.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
